en_184939_0	A schoolgirl from a school at Atabage in Udagama, Pussellawa has died after she fell sick nearby the school's dancing room.
en_184939_1	Our correspondent said the girl had complained of a headache at around 12.05 this afternoon (Mar. 02) and then had fainted.
en_184939_2	She had died upon admission to Gampola Hospital.
en_184939_3	The victim, a 15-year-old, was a resident of Panvilatenna and the body is kept at Gampola Hospital.
en_184939_4	Meanwhile, on Wednesday (Feb. 28), a 9-year-old girl died after she had collapsed at the school playground while taking part in a sports activity.
